tags: [[Reviewing Staging]]
title: Apply and Cancel
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

''Apply'' walks the staged rows top-to-bottom, executes each row's chosen action against the wiki, then clears the staging area.  The imported titles get appended to the audit log (see [[Audit Log]]).

''Cancel'' clears the staging area without writing anything.  No undo prompt -- if you weren't going to Apply, Cancel is cheap.

If any //rename// row is in an invalid state (see [[Renaming Rows]]), ''Apply'' is disabled and a red message at the top of the staging table points to the offending row.
